hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Is this a temporary or permanent position? pumped sports loaded Secondly, there’s the lack of irony in electoral campaigning. Admittedly, Germany doesn’t have a monopoly on this, as some of the peculiarly humourless hoardings from British elections past stand to prove (Tony Blair with demon eyes, anyone?). Yet German political parties don’t even try to come up with entertaining or engaging visual publicity: they simply paste the unflatteringly photographed faces of their candidates onto large billboards and stamp them with a few words unimaginatively plucked from the nearest thesaurus.
